<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-22"><hi rend="italic">August 22,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 15, Roumanian series.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 14 of
                            the 17th ultimo, Roumanian series, on the subject of the treatment of
                            Jews in Roumania, I inclose for your confidential information a copy of
                            an instruction<note n="a" xml:id="d841fna">Printed under Austria, <ref target="#pg_42">page 42</ref>.</note> which has been sent to the
                            diplomatic representatives of the United States in the countries parties
                            to the treaty of Berlin of July 13, 1878, in the hope that it may seem
                            wise to those powers to take measures to persuade the Government of
                            Roumania to accord to the indigenous Jews the generous and equal
                            treatment prescribed for them by the Berlin treaty.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>